      "writtenOn": "2019-09-24T22:02:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My understanding was that both \"time\" and \"times\" are specified, then \"time\" refers to the duration of the first run, and \"times\" refers to the duration of the remainder of the runs --- but this turned out to be mistaken, see https://logs.chromium.org/logs/chrome/buildbucket/cr-buildbucket.appspot.com/8903237483609759584/+/steps/performance_test_suite_on_Intel_GPU_on_Windows_on_Windows-10-16299.309/0/logs/json.output/0 (search for trace/traceEvents/tmpiqbp8e.json.gz, which is in the first test result)\n\nCorrect behavior:\n\nIf \"times\" is specified, then use it, as contains durations of all runs; ignore \"time\" if specified as it will be the first element of \"times\".\n\nIf only \"time\" is specified, then we only have the duration of the first run.\n\nWill fix in the open CL that added it.",
      "parentUuid": "c99d6d5b_d8affecd",
